aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 02, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kqj1665702890051.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kqj1665702890051.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kqj1665702890051.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kqj1665702890051\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Component Implementations\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"kqj1665702890051__component_implementations_109339\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The component signature specifies the implementation a component, which determines the technology used to deploy it, such as Uniface, C, or Java.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kqj1665702890051__p_d33950e1_d33951e1_d33952e1\">In theory, a component may have more than one implementation, making it possible for users to choose the implementation they want to use when the application is deployed. In this case, you can define a single signature that lists both implementations.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kqj1665702890051__p_d33953e1_d33954e1_d33955e1\">A component interface alone is not sufficient to deliver functionality. The functionality of a component is realized by specifying the implementation of the component. You can specify the component implementation using any of the Uniface component editors, or using another component construction tool.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kqj1665702890051__p_d33956e1_d33957e1_d33958e1\">Uniface provides call-in and call-out mechanisms that link the component into an application. The implementations you choose affect the operations that are available.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kqj1665702890051__p_d33959e1_d33960e1_d33961e1\">If a component has multiple implementations, you can specify a default implementation. At runtime, the default implementation is executed, unless the [SERVICES_EXEC] section of the <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.asn</span> file specifies that another implementation should be used.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Component Implementations</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__1\">Implementation type</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__2\">Operations available by default</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__3\">Editable</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__4\">Comments</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"2\"> Uniface Component </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__3\"> Y </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__4\"> These are built-in Uniface operations. You can\n                     define parameters for the <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code> operation only. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> , <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__3\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__4\"> These are explicit operations. If you define\n                     operations named <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code>  and <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>  they are\n                     activated implicitly. For more information on <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code>  and\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code> see <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">operation</span>. <p class=\"p\">You cannot\n                        define parameters for <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> and\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__1\"> C </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__4\">You can define the default operations\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code> , <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code> , and <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code>\n                     and the implicit operations <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>.\n                        <p class=\"p\">You cannot define parameters for <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code>,\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> or\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">However, if you define both 4GL and C implementations for a component, the\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code>\n                        parameters become available. If you then delete the 4GL implementation,\n                        these parameters remain available for the C implementation.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__1\"> COM </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__4\"> No default operations are available. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__1\"> Java Call-in </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__4\"> No default operations are available. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__1\"> Stored Procedure </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__4\"> No default operations are available. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__1\"> Operating System Service </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">COMMAND</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">COMMANDOUT</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kqj1665702890051__table_d3443e1_d3444e1_d3445e1__entry__4\"> Enter operating system commands using\n\t\t\t\t ProcScript to be executed via an Operating System Service. You can use your assignment file to\n\t\t\t\t redirect the Operating System Service components to a Uniface server. <p class=\"p\">The maximum length of a command is 511\n\t\t\t\t bytes.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/juz1692183224178.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Integrating with Other Technologies</a><p>The Uniface architecture enables you to integrate Uniface and non-Uniface components in a single application, and to deploy the application on a large variety of platforms and technologies.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ohx1665702678898.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define a Component Implementation</a><p>Each component can have one or more implementations.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529328\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529328\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Component Implementations Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 02, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Component Implementations The component signature specifies the implementation a component, which determines the technology used to deploy it, such as Uniface, C, or Java. In theory, a component may have more than one implementation, making it possible for users to choose the implementation they want to use when the application is deployed. In this case, you can define a single signature that lists both implementations. A component interface alone is not sufficient to deliver functionality. The functionality of a component is realized by specifying the implementation of the component. You can specify the component implementation using any of the Uniface component editors, or using another component construction tool. Uniface provides call-in and call-out mechanisms that link the component into an application. The implementations you choose affect the operations that are available. If a component has multiple implementations, you can specify a default implementation. At runtime, the default implementation is executed, unless the [SERVICES_EXEC] section of the usys.asn file specifies that another implementation should be used. Table 1. Component Implementations Implementation type Operations available by default Editable Comments Uniface Component ACCEPT , EXEC , QUIT Y These are built-in Uniface operations. You can define parameters for the EXEC operation only. INIT , CLEANUP These are explicit operations. If you define operations named INIT and CLEANUP they are activated implicitly. For more information on INIT and CLEANUP see operation . You cannot define parameters for INIT and CLEANUP . C None N You can define the default operations ACCEPT , QUIT , and EXEC and the implicit operations INIT and CLEANUP . You cannot define parameters for ACCEPT , QUIT , INIT or CLEANUP . However, if you define both 4GL and C implementations for a component, the ACCEPT , QUIT , and EXEC parameters become available. If you then delete the 4GL implementation, these parameters remain available for the C implementation. COM None N No default operations are available. Java Call-in None N No default operations are available. Stored Procedure None N No default operations are available. Operating System Service COMMAND , COMMANDOUT N Enter operating system commands using ProcScript to be executed via an Operating System Service. You can use your assignment file to redirect the Operating System Service components to a Uniface server. The maximum length of a command is 511 bytes. Related Links Integrating with Other Technologies The Uniface architecture enables you to integrate Uniface and non-Uniface components in a single application, and to deploy the application on a large variety of platforms and technologies. Define a Component Implementation Each component can have one or more implementations. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}